{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review guidance and fund training for psychiatric and mental health care staff",
        "additional_details": "We want Government to fund mandatory training for psychiatric and mental health care staff in trauma-informed and compassionate care, and increased access to talking therapies, peer support, and non-medication-based interventions. We believe hospitals sometimes respond to mental health crises with heavy medication and sedation, which we think is wrong.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to conduct a review of sedation and chemical restraint policies in psychiatric hospitals and mental health care facilities.",
